{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641188"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:24:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:24:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17869"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17869","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17869"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10583"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78717"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10583","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10583"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17869"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64060"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8405"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24670"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24673"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24674"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24675"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78717"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAdipose tissue exists in several distinct anatomical locations in the human body and serves multiple physiological functions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about adipose tissue distribution and function is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Men have greater leg subcutaneous fat stores than women","Ectopic fat includes fat stored within skeletal muscle","Subcutaneous fat primarily surrounds the internal organs","Visceral fat has lower metabolic activity than subcutaneous fat","Adipose tissue functions only as an energy storage depot"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEctopic fat includes fat stored within skeletal muscle\u003C/strong\u003E and other locations not typically associated with fat storage, such as the liver and pancreas. This type of fat accumulation is associated with metabolic dysfunction and insulin resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect statements can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMen have greater leg subcutaneous fat stores than women\u003C/strong\u003E - Women typically have greater subcutaneous fat stores in the gluteal-femoral region compared to men\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubcutaneous fat primarily surrounds the internal organs\u003C/strong\u003E - Subcutaneous fat is located beneath the skin, while visceral fat surrounds internal organs\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVisceral fat has lower metabolic activity than subcutaneous fat\u003C/strong\u003E - Visceral fat is more metabolically active and produces more inflammatory mediators than subcutaneous fat\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdipose tissue functions only as an energy storage depot\u003C/strong\u003E - Adipose tissue is an active endocrine organ that produces multiple hormones including leptin and adiponectin\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding adipose tissue distribution patterns is clinically relevant as different fat depots have distinct metabolic properties and health implications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Adipose tissue exists in different depots: subcutaneous (under skin), visceral (around organs), and ectopic (abnormal locations like muscle).","Women typically have more subcutaneous fat in gluteal and thigh regions, while men tend to accumulate more visceral fat.","Adipose tissue is an endocrine organ that produces hormones including leptin and adiponectin."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Chandel NS. Lipid Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Sep 1;13(9):a040576. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040576. PMID: 34470787; PMCID: PMC8411952","Wakil SJ, Abu-Elheiga LA. Fatty acid metabolism: target for metabolic syndrome. J Lipid Res. 2009 Apr;50 Suppl(Suppl):S138-43. doi: 10.1194/jlr.R800079-JLR200. Epub 2008 Dec 1. PMID: 19047759; PMCID: PMC2674721"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64060"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17869"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64060"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T14:58:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T14:59:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10583"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78717"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app